{"slug": "bumbleflower", "name": "Ms. Bumbleflower", "commander": "Ms. Bumbleflower", "colors": "Bant", "pips": ["W", "U", "G"], "archetype": "Spellslinger / tempo-control", "status": "Solid", "bracket": 3, "score": 15, "axes": [{"label": "Core loop", "score": 4}, {"label": "Kill reliability", "score": 3}, {"label": "Durability", "score": 3}, {"label": "Interaction", "score": 5}], "gc": [], "clock": {"decap": "T8", "table": "T11", "grid": [5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12, 14], "decapCurve": [0, 7, 38, 82, 96, 99, 100, 100], "tableCurve": [0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 17, 82, 97], "never": [0, 2], "src": "lab bmf_clock_lab @8k"}, "gamePlan": "Cast a high volume of cheap spells. Each cast triggers Bumbleflower, and the deck is built so that every part of that trigger feeds a payoff: the forced opponent-draw feeds \"opponents drawing\" payoffs, the second-resolution draw-two feeds \"you drawing\" payoffs, and the +1/+1 counter feeds \"counters placed\" payoffs \u2014 or steals a creature outright. The result is a tempo-control deck that buries the table in card advantage while picking apart their board, then closes slowly with an evasive, counter-pumped threat, a Jolrael alpha strike, or a stolen army.", "winLine": "Jolrael alpha strike (lands -> X/X, X = hand size)", "finishers": [{"name": "Jolrael Alpha Strike", "tag": "primary", "note": "With a full hand (routine for this deck) and a board of Cats, payoff creatures, and/or stolen bodies, Jolrael's {4}{G}{G} sets your team to X/X where X = cards in hand."}, {"name": "Willbreaker Theft, then Swing", "tag": "", "note": "With Willbreaker in play, aim Bumbleflower's counter at an opponent's creature each cast to steal it (and it gains flying that turn \u2014 can attack immediately)."}, {"name": "Evasive Counter Beats", "tag": "", "note": "A single creature (commander or a payoff body) accumulates a +1/+1 counter and flying every cast."}], "rulings": [{"name": "Bumbleflower's ability resolves BEFORE the spell that triggered it, and resolves even if that spell is countered.", "note": "The draw / counter / steal happens first \u2014 so a Willbreaker steal off your spell goes through even if the spell itself gets countered."}, {"name": "The \"draw two\" is on the second resolution each turn", "note": "cast at least two spells you trigger on. Free spells (Probe, Snap, Frantic Search) are how you reliably get there."}, {"name": "The counter and flying go to the same target creature; you pick it every cast.", "note": "Aim it at: (a) your evasive threat, (b) Dusk Legion Duelist / Fathom Mage to draw a card, or (c) an opponent's creature with Willbreaker out to steal it. You keep stolen creatures only while Willbreaker lives."}, {"name": "Willbreaker triggers on any of your targeted effects hitting an opponent's creature", "note": "Bumbleflower's counter, Ty Lee's tap, Generous Patron's support. Pongify/Path/Swords also target, but they destroy; use the non-lethal effects to steal."}, {"name": "The forced opponent-draw is a real cost \u2014 but you choose who.", "note": "Feed the least threatening player, or feed someone to turn on Faerie Mastermind (you draw on their 2nd draw), Smuggler's Share (draw per opponent who drew 2+), and Tataru Taru (Treasure when an opponent draws on your turn). Don't gift a draw-punisher (Nekusar) for free."}, {"name": "Jolrael's pump sets base P/T to cards-in-hand and overwrites", "note": "play it as a finisher with a full hand. Her Cat tokens come from your second draw each turn (which the commander's draw-two enables)."}, {"name": "Dress Down turns off ALL creature abilities, including yours", "note": "use it to blank an opponent's engine/combo, not while you're relying on your own creatures; it sacrifices itself at end step."}, {"name": "Generous Gift / Beast Within hand the target's controller a token", "note": "fine as removal, just count the body you're giving back."}], "composition": [{"name": "Steal & Combat Payoffs", "count": 5}, {"name": "Card-Draw Engine & Tax", "count": 8